photos.title: Lake of 7 Colors
photos.description: I think this is the closest i've come to seeing the 7 shades of blue.

photos.title: Old Chain New Chain
photos.description: If you can tell which chain is the new one and which is the old one, you're probably a qualified motorcycle mechanic.

photos.title: Tire Replacement
photos.description: Unfortunately, this mechanic is about to mess up my motorcycle, and I don't know it yet.

photos.title: Two Michiladas
photos.description: I have grown to love Michiladas, especially Mexican style. They've got lime, chile, salt, and worshtershire sauce.

photos.title: Fire
photos.description: Something was on fire. The Bacalar fire department showed up. The fire department seems to be theree guys in a pickup truck with a large plastic container of water, and some buckets.

photos.title: Harvesting Coconuts
photos.description: There were bunches of coconuts directly above where I wanted to sit in a hammock.  I rigged up a fairly reliable harness using some webbing and carabiners. It wasn't entirely comfortable, but I chopped down heaps of coconuts, then rested  safely in the shade of the tree and sipped some coconut water.

photos.title: Cow in Garage
photos.description: Someone parked their cow in the garage.

photos.title: Police KLR650
photos.description: Looks a bunch like my motorcycle, but has the extra police gizmos... And appears to be lowered.

photos.title: German Cycleists
photos.description: These beautiful people are riding bicycles with their two year old daughter from Alaska to Argentina. Life doesn't stop when you have kids I guess.

photos.title: Chiliaquilis
photos.description: Made this with Whitney for breakfast. Secret eggs in the bottom, and fresh made tortilla chips.

photos.title: Pipo
photos.description: Meet Pipo, the Italian cook in Bacalar. Great guy.

photos.title: Dog on Wall
photos.description: This dog was always up on this wall when I walked by, usually just napping there, of course when I stopped to take a photo, he got up to bark at me.
